word_mean_info__list.difference: 普通用词，侧重清楚明白。
语气较强，指极为明显，有目共睹，无需说明和论证。
指根据事实成为显然的。
强调显而易见或一想便知。这个词从动词appear派生而来，故有时含有表面如此而事实上未必的意味。
语义较强，书面用词，强调一目了然，暗示不要任何推论就一清二楚。
语气肯定，着重明白无误，无可怀疑。
普通用词，含义与clear很接近，可通用，但plain着重简单明了，不复杂。
较正式用词，指轮廓的清楚或定义、含义的明确，不会弄错。

bilingual.source: It is evident that she is very talented in music.

bilingual.source: His excitement was evident when he received the award.
bilingual.target: 当他领奖时，他的兴奋是明显的。

bilingual.source: His actions had religious overtones that were quite evident.
bilingual.target: 他的行为有明显的宗教潜在的含义。

bilingual.source: The difference in quality is evident between the two products.
bilingual.target: 两种产品之间的质量差异是明显的。

bilingual.source: Her compassion was evident when she volunteered at the shelter.
bilingual.target: 她在收容所做志愿者时表现出了明显的同情心。

bilingual.source: The community's espoir was evident during the rebuilding process.

bilingual.source: She has an artistic talent that is evident in her paintings.
